# Security logging

Source: **`owasp_secure_coding_hardening_plan.md`** Phase 5; helpers **`GoDiveSecurityEvent`**, **`GoDiveSecurityEventJournal`**, **`SecurityEventRecord`**.

## Do

- Record coarse **`GoDiveSecurityEvent`** for: auth success/fail, sign-out, account delete, import reject, CDN checksum / refresh fail.
- Event **details** are short tokens only (`fit.contentTypeMismatch`, `firebase`) — scrub via **`GoDiveSecurityEvent.sanitizedDetail`**.
- Persist to the **user-store** journal when a signed-in **`ownerProfileID`** is known (Keychain or explicit). Pre-auth / post-wipe: OSLog only (`persistToJournal: false` when needed).
- Opt-in developer share: **`AppUserSettings.shareSecurityEvents`** (device-local) → **`SecurityEventCloudUploader`** with **`CrashReportPayloadScrubber`**; never upload **`ownerProfileID`**.
- User-facing failures: **`GoDiveUserFacingError`** / **`AccountSession.signInFailureUserMessage`** — never `String(describing:)` or raw SDK errors in Release UI.
- Prefer **`Logger`** with **`.private`** for UIDs, emails, tokens, GPS, site names, dive notes.

## Do not

- Log tokens, Apple identity tokens, Firebase ID tokens, or `Authorization` headers (see **`GoDiveSecretLogging`**).
- Enable verbose `*Debug` loggers in Release by default (gate with **`#if DEBUG`**).
- Use **`.public`** for PII in production-facing categories (**`Security`**, **`AccountSession`**, **`FirebaseAuth`**).
- Sync **`shareSecurityEvents`** / **`shareCrashReports`** through **`UserPreferences`** CloudKit (keep device-local).
